(ABSTRACT) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This document defines how cyberspace protects itself. The model is) show newline
(simple: capabilities all the way down. Objects are content.) show newline
(Authorization flows through signed certificates. No labels, no ACLs, no) show newline
(ambient authority. You hold a capability or you don't.) show newline
() show newline
(We use the rigor of TCSEC B2 as a lens - particularly for covert channel) show newline
(analysis - but cyberspace is its own thing. This is our security) show newline
(architecture, in our language.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
