(INFORMATION FLOW) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The mathematics of multilevel security, expressed in capabilities.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(The Properties) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
(Traditional formulations speak of "read up" and "write down" with) show newline
(respect to classification labels. We preserve the mathematics but speak) show newline
(differently:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Traditional       Cyberspace                  Formal Statement                                      ) show newline
(  "No read up"      Read requires capability    ∀ read\(P,O\): P ∈ holders\(cap_read\(O\)\)             ) show newline
(  "No write down"   Write requires capability   ∀ write\(P,O\): P ∈ holders\(cap_write\(O\)\)           ) show newline
(  "No read down"    Integrity via provenance    ∀ accept\(P,O\): verify\(signature\(O\)\)                 ) show newline
(  "No write up"     Attenuation only            ∀ delegate\(P₁,P₂,C\): C ⊆ capabilities\(P₁\)   ) show newline
() show newline
(The capability graph IS the lattice. Delegation flows down. Authority) show newline
(cannot flow up.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Beyond Bell-LaPadula and Biba) show newline
(-----------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Bell-LaPadula \(1973\) and Biba \(1977\) formalized information flow as) show newline
(lattice properties enforced by a central reference monitor. Both) show newline
(require:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Security labels attached to subjects and objects) show newline
(  * A trusted reference monitor that mediates all access) show newline
(  * Hierarchical classification \(UNCLASSIFIED < SECRET < TOP SECRET\)) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace inverts this architecture:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Traditional MAC                   Capability-Based Flow                  ) show newline
(  Labels on objects                 No labels—objects are just content   ) show newline
(  Central reference monitor         Decentralized verification             ) show newline
(  Policy in the monitor             Policy in the certificates             ) show newline
(  Lattice of security levels        Graph of capability delegation         ) show newline
(  Clearance assigned by authority   Capability granted by delegation       ) show newline
() show newline
(The key insight: information flow is measurable. Every channel has) show newline
(bandwidth—bits per second, bytes per second. Shannon's information) show newline
(theory applies. If you can measure the flow, you can reason about where) show newline
(information leaks.) show newline
() show newline
(In capability systems, the flow is explicit: you hold a capability or) show newline
(you don't. The audit trail records every exercise. Covert channels) show newline
(remain \(timing, storage\), but the overt channels are precisely the) show newline
(capability graph. No hidden ambient authority. No implicit flows through) show newline
(the reference monitor's state.) show newline
() show newline
(This is not weaker than MAC—it's differently shaped. Bell-LaPadula) show newline
(prevents "read up" by checking labels; capabilities prevent it by) show newline
(requiring possession. The math is equivalent; the architecture is) show newline
(decentralized.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Confidentiality) show newline
(---------------) show newline
() show newline
(Information flows only through capabilities:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ∀ read\(P,O\): P ∈ holders\(capread\(O\)\)) show newline
(    ∀ write\(P,O\): P ∈ holders\(capwrite\(O\)\)) show newline
(    ∀ delegate\(P₁,P₂,C\): C ⊆ capabilities\(P₁\)) show newline
() show newline
(A principal without read capability cannot observe content. A principal) show newline
(without write capability cannot exfiltrate via storage. Delegation) show newline
(cannot grant what you don't hold.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Integrity) show newline
(---------) show newline
() show newline
(Modification flows only through capabilities:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ∀ modify\(P,O\): P ∈ holders\(capwrite\(O\)\)) show newline
(    ∀ delegate\(P₁,P₂,C'\): integrity\(C'\) ≤ integrity\(C\)) show newline
(    ∀ capability C: provenance\(C\) ⊆ audittrail) show newline
() show newline
(Objects cannot be corrupted without write capability. Delegated) show newline
(capabilities cannot exceed held capabilities. All grants are traceable.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Confinement) show newline
(-----------) show newline
() show newline
(The capability discipline eliminates ambient authority:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ∀ access\(P,O\): ∃ C ∈ capabilities\(P\): authorizes\(C,O\)) show newline
(    ∀ C: unforgeable\(C\)) show newline
(    ∀ acquire\(P,C\): ∃ P': delegate\(P',P,C\) ∨ create\(P,O\)) show newline
() show newline
(No access without explicit capability. Capabilities cannot be) show newline
(manufactured. The only paths: receive via delegation, or create the) show newline
(object.) show newline
