(UNLINKABILITY) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Chaum's insight \(1983\): you can prove authorization without revealing) show newline
(identity. Blind signatures create credentials that are verifiable but) show newline
(unlinkable - the issuer cannot connect the credential to the) show newline
(presentation.) show newline
() show newline
(This creates architectural tension with audit trails. Cyberspace values) show newline
(both accountability and privacy. The resolution: capabilities come in) show newline
(two forms.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Registered vs Bearer Capabilities) show newline
(---------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Property        Registered \(SPKI\)      Bearer \(Blinded\)     ) show newline
(  Subject field   Principal identified   Anonymous holder     ) show newline
(  Audit trail     Who did what           What was done        ) show newline
(  Revocation      By subject             By capability hash   ) show newline
(  Delegation      To named principals    Not delegable        ) show newline
(  Use case        Accountability         Privacy              ) show newline
() show newline
(Registered capabilities are checks - they name the bearer. Bearer) show newline
(capabilities are cash - whoever holds them can spend them.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Blind Signature Protocol) show newline
(------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Alice wants to exercise a capability without revealing she's Alice:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    1. Alice proves to Issuer she holds capability C) show newline
(    2. Alice generates random blinding factor r) show newline
(    3. Alice computes blinded = blind\(token, r\)) show newline
(    4. Issuer signs: sig = sign\(blinded\)) show newline
(    5. Alice unblinds: bearer_sig = unblind\(sig, r\)) show newline
(    6. Alice presents \(token, bearer_sig\) anonymously) show newline
(    7. Verifier confirms Issuer's signature without learning Alice's identity) show newline
() show newline
(The Issuer knows Alice was authorized \(step 1\) but cannot link the) show newline
(bearer credential \(step 6\) to Alice. Unlinkability is mathematical, not) show newline
(policy.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace Integration) show newline
(----------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ;; Request blinded capability \(proves eligibility, gets blind-signed token\)) show newline
(    \(define \(capability-blind issuer tag\)) show newline
(      "Get bearer capability for tag, unlinkable to principal") show newline
(      \(let* \(\(token \(random-bytes 32\)\)) show newline
(             \(r \(blind-factor-generate\)\)) show newline
(             \(blinded \(blind token r\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Prove we hold registered capability for this tag) show newline
(        ;; Issuer signs blinded token) show newline
(        \(let \(\(blind-sig \(issuer-sign-blinded issuer blinded tag\)\)\)) show newline
(          ;; Unblind locally) show newline
(          \(make-bearer-capability) show newline
(            token: token) show newline
(            signature: \(unblind blind-sig r\)) show newline
(            tag: tag) show newline
(            issuer: issuer\)\)\)\)) show newline
(    ;; Exercise bearer capability) show newline
(    \(define \(capability-exercise-bearer cap object\)) show newline
(      "Exercise capability without revealing identity") show newline
(      \(let \(\(token \(bearer-capability-token cap\)\)) show newline
(            \(sig \(bearer-capability-signature cap\)\)) show newline
(            \(tag \(bearer-capability-tag cap\)\)) show newline
(            \(issuer \(bearer-capability-issuer cap\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Verify issuer signed this token for this tag) show newline
(        \(unless \(blind-signature-verify issuer token sig tag\)) show newline
(          \(error 'invalid-bearer-capability\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Audit records capability exercise, not principal) show newline
(        \(audit-append action: 'bearer-exercise) show newline
(                      capability: \(sha512 token\)) show newline
(                      tag: tag) show newline
(                      actor: 'anonymous\)) show newline
(        ;; Perform operation) show newline
(        \(perform-operation tag object\)\)\)) show newline
() show newline
(The audit trail records that a valid bearer capability was exercised,) show newline
(but not who exercised it. The capability hash enables revocation without) show newline
(identification.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Use Cases) show newline
(---------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Operation                  Why Unlinkability                                 ) show newline
(  Quorum voting              Prove eligibility without linking vote to voter   ) show newline
(  Whistleblower submission   Submit evidence without identification            ) show newline
(  Anonymous reads            Access sensitive content without tracking         ) show newline
(  Credential presentation    Prove role without revealing principal            ) show newline
(  Rate-limited tokens        Prevent abuse without profiling users             ) show newline
() show newline
(Non-use-cases \(accountability required\):) show newline
() show newline
(  * Writes - usually need to know who modified) show newline
(  * Delegation - must name the delegate) show newline
(  * Administrative actions - audit trail essential) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(The Tradeoff) show newline
(------------) show newline
() show newline
(Bearer capabilities sacrifice traceability for privacy. Once issued, the) show newline
(issuer cannot:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Determine who exercised the capability) show newline
(  * Link multiple exercises to the same principal) show newline
(  * Revoke based on principal \(only by capability hash\)) show newline
() show newline
(This is the point. Chaum solved the double-spending problem for digital) show newline
(cash without a public ledger - the bank couldn't track who spent what.) show newline
(Bitcoin retreated from this by making all transactions public.) show newline
(Cyberspace preserves the choice: registered capabilities when you need) show newline
(accountability, bearer capabilities when you need privacy.) show newline
() show newline
(The axioms still hold:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    A1. No Ambient Authority - still need a capability) show newline
(    A2. Capabilities Are Unforgeable - blind signatures are Ed25519) show newline
(    A3. Capabilities Only Attenuate - bearer caps cannot delegate) show newline
(    A4. Objects Are Immutable - unchanged) show newline
() show newline
(Unlinkability is orthogonal to authorization. You still need permission;) show newline
(you just don't have to identify yourself to use it.) show newline
() show newline
