(SECURE ERASURE) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(When sensitive data must be destroyed, it must be destroyed completely.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Erasure Requirements) show newline
(--------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  What               How                                   Verification           ) show newline
(  Object content     Overwrite with random, then zeros     Read-back verify       ) show newline
(  Memory buffers     Secure memset, compiler barrier       Not optimized away     ) show newline
(  Key material       Zeroize immediately after use         Audit trail entry      ) show newline
(  Audit entries      Preserve hash chain, redact content   Chain integrity        ) show newline
(  Capability certs   Revoke, then destroy                  Revocation published   ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Erasure Guarantees) show newline
(------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    E1. Zeroization is atomic) show newline
(        erase\(o\) → ¬recoverable\(o\)) show newline
(    E2. Memory clearing defeats inspection) show newline
(        clear\(buffer\) → ∀ address ∈ buffer: read\(address\) = 0) show newline
(    E3. Key destruction is immediate) show newline
(        destroy\(key\) → ¬usable\(key\) ∧ audit\(destroyed, key\)) show newline
(    E4. Revocation propagates) show newline
(        revoke\(cert\) → ∀ delegate\(cert, c'\): revoke\(c'\)) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Implementation) show newline
(--------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ;; Secure memory clearing \(defeats compiler optimization\)) show newline
(    \(define \(secure-clear! buffer\)) show newline
(      "Overwrite buffer with zeros, verify") show newline
(      \(let \(\(len \(blob-size buffer\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Write zeros) show newline
(        \(do \(\(i 0 \(+ i 1\)\)\)) show newline
(            \(\(>= i len\)\)) show newline
(          \(blob-set! buffer i 0\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Memory barrier \(implementation-specific\)) show newline
(        ;; Verify) show newline
(        \(do \(\(i 0 \(+ i 1\)\)\)) show newline
(            \(\(>= i len\) #t\)) show newline
(          \(unless \(zero? \(blob-ref buffer i\)\)) show newline
(            \(error 'secure-clear-failed\)\)\)\)\)) show newline
(    ;; Key zeroization) show newline
(    \(define \(key-destroy! key\)) show newline
(      "Zeroize key material, audit") show newline
(      \(let \(\(material \(key-material key\)\)\)) show newline
(        \(secure-clear! material\)) show newline
(        \(audit-append actor: \(current-principal\)) show newline
(                      action: 'key-destroyed) show newline
(                      target: \(key-id key\)\)) show newline
(        'destroyed\)\)) show newline
(    ;; Object secure deletion) show newline
(    \(define \(object-erase! hash\)) show newline
(      "Securely erase object content") show newline
(      \(let \(\(path \(vault-object-path hash\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Overwrite with random) show newline
(        \(call-with-output-file path) show newline
(          \(lambda \(port\)) show newline
(            \(write-blob port \(random-bytes \(file-size path\)\)\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Overwrite with zeros) show newline
(        \(call-with-output-file path) show newline
(          \(lambda \(port\)) show newline
(            \(write-blob port \(make-blob \(file-size path\) 0\)\)\)\)) show newline
(        ;; Delete) show newline
(        \(delete-file path\)) show newline
(        ;; Audit) show newline
(        \(audit-append actor: \(current-principal\)) show newline
(                      action: 'object-erased) show newline
(                      target: hash\)) show newline
(        'erased\)\)) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(What Cannot Be Erased) show newline
(---------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Some things must persist:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Thing                   Why                             ) show newline
(  Audit chain structure   Hash links must verify          ) show newline
(  Revocation records      Must prove capability invalid   ) show newline
(  Content hashes          May exist in other chains       ) show newline
() show newline
(Redaction, not deletion: the fact that something existed remains, but) show newline
(the content is gone.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(SSD/Flash Considerations) show newline
(------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Modern storage complicates secure erasure:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Wear leveling moves data without notification) show newline
(  * Trim/discard doesn't guarantee overwrite) show newline
(  * Encryption is the only reliable approach) show newline
() show newline
(Our answer: Encrypt at rest \(Memo-030\). Erasing the key erases the data.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    ;; With encryption at rest, key destruction = data destruction) show newline
(    \(define \(secure-erase-encrypted hash\)) show newline
(      "For encrypted objects: destroy decryption key") show newline
(      \(let \(\(dek \(object-data-encryption-key hash\)\)\)) show newline
(        \(key-destroy! dek\)) show newline
(        ;; The ciphertext remains but is now meaningless) show newline
(        'erased-via-key-destruction\)\)) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
