(COVERT CHANNELS) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This is where we get serious.) show newline
() show newline
(A covert channel is information flow that violates policy - a way to) show newline
(leak data that bypasses the capability model. They exist in every) show newline
(system. We analyze ours.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Storage Channels) show newline
(----------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Channel            How It Works                        Bandwidth      Mitigation           ) show newline
(  Object existence   Create/don't create object as 1/0   ~1 bit/op      Bloom filter noise   ) show newline
(  Object size        Encode in padding                   ~10 bits/obj   Size quantization    ) show newline
(  Object count       Number of objects in namespace      ~4 bits/ns     Rate limiting        ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Timing Channels) show newline
(---------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Channel             How It Works                Bandwidth      Mitigation          ) show newline
(  Verification time   Slow/fast response as 1/0   ~1 bit/100ms   Constant-time ops   ) show newline
(  Network latency     Delay patterns              ~10 bits/sec   Batching, Tor       ) show newline
(  Audit write time    When entries appear         ~1 bit/sec     Async, batched      ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Federation Channels) show newline
(-------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Channel           How It Works              Bandwidth       Mitigation          ) show newline
(  Sync timing       When objects replicate    ~1 bit/sync     Random delays       ) show newline
(  Peer selection    Which realms to contact   ~4 bits/conn    Randomized peers    ) show newline
(  Gossip patterns   Propagation paths         ~2 bits/round   Epidemic flooding   ) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Analysis) show newline
(--------) show newline
() show newline
(Scenario: Alice has SECRET access. Bob has UNCLASSIFIED. Alice wants to) show newline
(leak to Bob.) show newline
() show newline
(Via storage: Alice creates/deletes objects Bob can see. Each operation) show newline
(signals one bit. Rate: maybe 1 bit/second with careful timing.) show newline
() show newline
(Via timing: Alice influences verification time of requests Bob makes.) show newline
(Bob measures. Rate: maybe 0.1 bit/second, noisy.) show newline
() show newline
(Via federation: Alice causes sync events Bob can observe. Rate: depends) show newline
(on federation config, maybe 0.01 bit/second.) show newline
() show newline
(Assessment: Total covert bandwidth: ~1-2 bits/second under ideal) show newline
(conditions. Not enough for bulk data. Enough for short signals.) show newline
(Acceptable residual risk for our threat model.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(Mitigation Principles) show newline
(---------------------) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    1. Add noise where practical \(bloom filters, random delays\)) show newline
(    2. Quantize where observable \(object sizes, batch windows\)) show newline
(    3. Rate limit where controllable \(operations per time\)) show newline
(    4. Accept what remains \(document it, move on\)) show newline
